{"_id": "28707126|None", "id": "28707126", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Immunol. Res.; 2017 08; 65(4) 951-956. doi:10.1007/s12026-017-8935-x", "year": "2017", "type": "title", "authors": "Zhou A, Liu X, Xia T, Li F, Wang J, Li J", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Estrogen receptor alpha gene (ESR1) polymorphism and its interaction with smoking and drinking contribute to susceptibility of systemic lupus erythematosus.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "2099", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "47906"}, "text": "Estrogen receptor alpha", "locations": [{"offset": 0, "length": 23}]}, {"id": "4", "infons": {"identifier": "2099", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "47906"}, "text": "ESR1", "locations": [{"offset": 30, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "5", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D008180", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "systemic lupus erythematosus", "locations": [{"offset": 127, "length": 28}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 157, "text": "The aim of this study is to investigate the association of estrogen receptor alpha gene (ESR1) polymorphisms, additional gene-gene, and gene-environment interaction with systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE) risk. SNPStats (available online at http://bioinfo.iconcologia.net/SNPstats ) was used to investigate the Hardy-Weinberg equilibrium (HWE) in controls and association between SNP and SLE risk. Generalized multifactor dimensionality reduction (GMDR) was used to screen the interactions among SNPs and environmental risk factors; SLE risk was significantly higher in carriers of rs2234693 C allele than those with TT (TC + CC versus TT), adjusted OR (95%CI) = 1.57 (1.21-2.06), and was also higher in carriers of rs9340799 G allele than those with AA (AG + GG versus AA), adjusted OR (95%CI) = 1.68 (1.24-2.13). However, we also find no association between rs2228480 and SLE risk after covariates adjustment. We found a significant two-locus model (p = 0.0010) involving rs2234693 and smoking; the cross-validation consistency of this model was 10/10, and the testing accuracy was 62.70%. Smokers with TC or CC of rs2234693 genotype have the highest SLE risk, compared to never-smokers with TT of rs2234693 genotype, OR (95%CI) was 2.50 (1.65-3.42), after covariates adjustment for gender, age, alcohol drinking, and BMI. We found that C allele of rs2234693 and G allele of rs9340799 within ESR1 gene, their interaction between rs2234693 and current smoking were all associated with increased SLE risk.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "27", "infons": {"identifier": "2099", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "47906"}, "text": "estrogen receptor alpha", "locations": [{"offset": 216, "length": 23}]}, {"id": "28", "infons": {"identifier": "2099", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "47906"}, "text": "ESR1", "locations": [{"offset": 246, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "29", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D008180", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "systemic lupus erythematosus", "locations": [{"offset": 327, "length": 28}]}, {"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D008180", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "SLE", "locations": [{"offset": 357, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D008180", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "SLE", "locations": [{"offset": 545, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "32", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D008180", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "SLE", "locations": [{"offset": 690, "length": 3}]}, {"id": "33", "infons": {"identifier": "rs2234693", "type": "Mutation", "subtype": "SNP"}, "text": "rs2234693", "locations": [{"offset": 739, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "34", "infons": {"identifier": "rs9340799", "type": "Mutation", "subtype": "SNP"}, "text": "rs9340799", "locations": [{"offset": 873, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "35", "infons": {"identifier": "rs2228480", "type": "Mutation", "subtype": "SNP"}, "text": "rs2228480", "locations": [{"offset": 1017, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "36", "infons": {"id